All in again. REFERENDUM: Not enough time, neither politically nor technically. ELECTION: There's a very tight window between the vote on May's deal in the week commencing 14 Jan 2019 and the last day a vote of no confidence can happen, which is 5 Feb 2019. So the chances of an election would reduce linearly due to passage of time on a daily basis from say 16 Jan 2019 to 5 Feb 2019. Three weeks. But an election can only happen if;
1. the Government loses a vote of no confidence (very unlikely).
2. it takes place within very nearly the absolute minimum time allowed by statute (extremely unlikely especially given the chaos that would follow if point 1 occurred.) So an election would require two very unlikely things to happen.
